						<summary>

						<p>On the wall of the Mallikārjuna temple.</p>						

						<p>1076 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 998, Naḷa, Saṅkrānti, Sunday. In the said cyclic year corresponding to 1076 A.D., Tulā-saṁkrānti occurred on Sunday, in which case the date corresponds to 1076 A.D., September 25.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift to the god Kalidēva by Saṁkarakōṭi, disciple of Dēvēndrapaṇḍita. <hi rend="italic">Rūvāri</hi> Kētōja engraved the record.</p>						

						</summary>
